`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The ordering here is intentional: `auto` first (most common default), then `pointer`/`default` (most frequently used), then interaction cursors (`text`, `move`, `grab`/`grabbing`), then feedback cursors (`not-allowed`, `crosshair`, `wait`, `help`), then zoom, and finally `none`. This groups them by usage frequency rather than alphabetically, which is better UX for a design tool dropdown.
